The paper deals with the intersection of Computer Vision and Natural Language, specifically in grounding the components of a structured description in an image. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Computer Vision (cs.CV), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, Computer Vision and Computational Linguistics are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the paper's main focus. Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence are also likely categories, as the paper proposes a novel approach to learning grounding using adversarial feedback. Multimedia is a less likely category, but still possible given the paper's focus on multi-modal translation.
